    executive: '<em>Key Points:</em> <em>   Research suggests the General Organization for Social Insurance (GOSI) manages assets totaling approximately SAR 1.2 trillion (USD 320 billion to USD 374 billion), making it the eighth-largest public pension fund globally .  </em>   Unlike the Public Investment Fund (PIF), which operates as a developmental Sovereign Wealth Fund (SWF), GOSI functions strictly as a Sovereign Pension Reserve Fund. Its investment thesis revolves around Liability-Driven Investment (LDI) to meet long-term demographic obligations . <em>   The portfolio allocation leans heavily toward capital preservation, with fixed income comprising an estimated 50% of the portfolio, public equities at 17%, and alternative investments (private equity, real estate, infrastructure) expanding rapidly to approximately 18% . </em>   GOSI deploys its capital through a bifurcated operational model: domestic investments are largely managed internally, anchoring the Saudi Stock Exchange (Tadawul), while international allocations are executed via external partnerships with top-tier global asset managers . *   Recent activity between 2024 and 2026 demonstrates an aggressive expansion into global private markets and climate transition, evidenced by a $1.5 billion commitment to TPG Rise Climate funds and massive strategic joint ventures with PIF entities like AviLease .',
