    executive: '<p>The financial architecture of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia is currently undergoing a profound transformation, driven by the imperatives of Vision 2030. At the epicenter of this structural shift is Saudi National Bank (SNB) and its investment banking and asset management subsidiary, <strong>SNB Capital</strong>. Formed in April 2021 through the mega-merger of National Commercial Bank (NCB) and Samba Financial Group, SNB operates as the undisputed banking heavyweight of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) . SNB Capital, licensed by the Capital Market Authority (CMA), operates across five core business lines: Asset Management, Wealth Management, Securities, Investment Banking, and Principal Investments . </p><p>This report provides an exhaustive, multi-dimensional analysis of SNB Capital. It addresses the institution\'s portfolio breakdowns, investment strategies, key holdings, sector allocations, geographical focus, sovereign relationships, recent market activities, corporate governance, and its indispensable role in realizing the economic objectives of Vision 2030.</p>',
