    executive: '<p><strong>AUM and Scale</strong>: Evidence indicates that Jadwa Investment manages approximately USD 30 billion (SAR 110 billion) in client assets, positioning it as one of the preeminent investment management and advisory firms in the Middle East . <strong>Corporate Identity</strong>: It appears to operate as a prominent Saudi closed joint-stock company, heavily engaged in alternative investments, private equity, and real estate, catering to government entities, institutional investors, and high-net-worth individuals . <strong>Sharia-Compliant Mandate</strong>: Research suggests that 100% of Jadwa\'s investment vehicles and operations strictly adhere to Islamic finance principles, overseen by an internal Shariah Supervisory Board . <strong>Recent Alternative Capital Expansion</strong>: The firm\'s 2024–2026 trajectory heavily emphasizes alternative asset classes, highlighted by a SAR 9 billion real estate commitment in late 2024 and the launch of a USD 200 million blind-pool private credit fund in early 2026 . <strong>Vision 2030 Integration</strong>: The evidence leans toward Jadwa acting as a critical private-sector conduit for Saudi Vision 2030, executing investments that directly advance national objectives in digitization, home ownership, and non-oil GDP diversification .</p>',
