    executive: '<strong>Key Points</strong> <em>   <strong>Asset Under Management (AUM):</strong> Research indicates that the specific Al Qasimi Family Office, owned by His Royal Highness Sheikh Ahmed bin Faisal Al Qasimi, manages an estimated USD 15 billion in assets .  </em>   <strong>Investment Ecosystem:</strong> It is important to recognize that the family\'s wealth is distributed across several royal private offices, single-family offices (like the Al Qasimi Group), and state-affiliated sovereign vehicles (such as the Sharjah Investment and Development Authority, or Shurooq) . <em>   <strong>Sector Focus:</strong> The portfolio appears heavily weighted toward real estate, financial services, education, media, and publishing, reflecting the strategic priorities of the Sharjah emirate .  </em>   <strong>Strategic Positioning:</strong> Evidence strongly suggests that Sharjah positions itself as the "Cultural Capital" of the region, focusing on heritage, family-friendly environments, and affordable value-driven real estate, in direct contrast to the luxury-driven, fast-paced commercial focus of Dubai and Abu Dhabi . *   <strong>Data Limitations:</strong> Exact sector allocation percentages and geographical distributions of private family wealth are not fully disclosed in public records. The percentages and allocations presented in this report represent estimated ranges synthesized from the best available research, holding portfolios, and historical investment patterns.',
