    timeline: '<p>A prime example of the firm\'s exit capability is <strong>Metito</strong>, a global provider of water desalination and wastewater management. Gulf Capital won the "Best Mid-market Deal of the Year" in 2007 for acquiring a 60% stake in the firm . Over a 17-year holding period, Gulf Capital institutionalized the company, expanded it globally, sold a minority stake to Mitsubishi in 2014, and finally orchestrated a consortium sale of a 62% stake to Abu Dhabi\'s Alpha Dhabi Holding in September 2023, reportedly making nearly four times its invested capital .</p><p>Similarly, in late 2022, Gulf Capital exited <strong>Chef Middle East</strong>—a premier foodservice distributor—via a highly profitable USD 100 million sale to The Chefs\' Warehouse, a Nasdaq-listed specialty food distributor looking to enter the GCC .</p><p></p>',
