  33: {
    executive: '<strong>Key Points</strong> <em>   <strong>Fund Profile:</strong> The Saudi Venture Capital Company (SVC) operates as a highly influential government-backed fund of funds and direct co-investment vehicle. </em>   <strong>Mandate:</strong> Research suggests it is a cornerstone of Saudi Arabia\'s Vision 2030, designed to stimulate and sustain financing for startups and SMEs from pre-seed to pre-IPO stages.  <em>   <strong>Capital Base:</strong> The evidence leans toward an active Assets Under Management (AUM) profile of approximately USD 1.6 billion (SAR 6 billion), with some reports indicating deployed or managed capital metrics scaling up to USD 2.2 billion in holistic ecosystem commitments. </em>   <strong>Sector Focus:</strong> Sector allocation appears to be strategically aligned with national digitization and infrastructure goals, heavily favoring E-commerce, Fintech, Enterprise Software, and EdTech.  *   <strong>Recent Activity:</strong> It seems likely that SVC’s 2024–2026 strategic initiatives, including the deployment of the "Aian" AI intelligence platform and crossing the SAR 4.5 billion committed capital threshold, have fundamentally cemented Saudi Arabia\'s position as the leading venture capital market in the MENA region.',
    mandateDetail: '<p>SVC is not structured as a conventional sovereign wealth fund—a role occupied primarily by the Public Investment Fund (PIF) and its multi-hundred-billion-dollar global and domestic portfolios . Instead, SVC operates under a highly specialized <strong>Fund of Funds and Co-Investment mandate</strong>, positioning itself as a catalytic investor and market maker . </p><p>Its investment operations are bifurcated into two primary programs:</p><p>1. <strong>Investment in Funds Program:</strong> This is the cornerstone of SVC\'s operational model, historically accounting for approximately 90% of its capital allocation . SVC invests as a Limited Partner (LP) in a wide spectrum of private capital vehicles, including venture capital (VC) funds, private equity (PE) funds, venture debt funds, private debt funds, startup studios, and accelerator funds . The objective is to lower the barriers to entry for fund managers looking to operate in the Saudi market and to scale the availability of institutional capital . To ensure crowding-in rather than crowding-out of private capital, SVC\'s participation in any single fund is capped at a maximum of 65% of the total fund size . This 65% ceiling also applies to the aggregate contribution of all Saudi government-related entities combined . 2. <strong>Co-Investment in Startups Program:</strong> Representing the remaining portion of its allocation, SVC co-invests directly alongside angel investors, institutional fund managers, and sophisticated investors . This program is designed to bridge specific funding gaps—such as early-stage pre-seed rounds or capital-intensive growth stages—and to stimulate investments in strategic sectors . For direct investments, SVC requires a minimum ticket size of SAR 1,000,000 (approximately USD 267,000) and caps its contribution at 30% of any given funding round . Furthermore, institutional co-investment matching is typically conducted on a 1:1 ratio .</p>',
    timeline: '<p>Deployment timeline data being compiled from research.</p>',
    macroContext: '<p>Macro context analysis pending integration.</p>',
    relatedFunds: [1, 6, 8, 12]
  },
