    executive: 'It seems likely that the venture capital landscape in the Middle East and North Africa (MENA) is undergoing a structural paradigm shift, driven significantly by state-affiliated actors and sovereign wealth ecosystems. Research suggests that Saudi Technology Ventures (STV) is at the epicenter of this transformation. Backed by Saudi Telecom Company (STC) and operating with an estimated $1.4 billion in Assets Under Management (AUM), STV appears to function as a critical bridge between early-stage startup innovation and late-stage institutional capital. The evidence leans toward STV playing a foundational role in actualizing Saudi Arabia\'s Vision 2030 by filling the historically persistent Series A to C funding gap.',
